Good. So `WriteObjectValue<T>` is already available and AOT-friendly (uses IJsonModel<T>). 

Now for the deserialization pattern, each type has a static `Deserialize*` method. The typical pattern is:
```csharp
// Before:
systemData = JsonSerializer.Deserialize<SystemData>(property.Value.GetRawText());
// After:
systemData = SystemData.DeserializeSystemData(property.Value);
```

But wait, `ResponseError` is from `Azure.Core`, not from this project. Let me check if it has IJsonModel or Deserialize methods accessible here.


I need to verify whether `ResponseError` implements `IJsonModel`.

